      "value": "What is JavaScript Optimization?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "JavaScript optimization is the process of improving how JavaScript files are loaded, executed, and delivered to reduce load time and improve performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why JavaScript Optimization Matters"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Heavy JavaScript can block rendering and delay interactivity. Optimizing JavaScript improves page speed, responsiveness, and user experience."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Minifying JavaScript"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "// Before\nfunction greet(name) {\n  console.log('Hello ' + name);\n}\n\n// After\nfunction greet(n){console.log('Hello '+n)}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Code Splitting"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Split JavaScript into smaller chunks and load only when needed."
    },
